'''Cannon Cadets''' is a gaming app developed by [[Ray Sharma]]'s [[XMG Studio]] for the [[iPhone]] and [[iPod Touch]]. It was officially released in the [[iTunes App Store]] on August 11, 2010.
{{Infobox video game | title = Cannon Cadets | image = Cannon Cadets icon.png | caption = Cannon Cadets icon | developer = [[XMG Studio]] | publisher = [[XMG Studio]] | released = August 11, 2010 | genre = Gaming, Family & Arcade | modes = Single Player | platforms = [[iPod Touch]], [[iPhone]], [[iPad]] }}
== Game Premise == Users unlock several characters while progressing through the 80+ levels. Gamers initially start out playing as RocketBoy and must save the rest of the Cadets, RocketGirl, Pop and Granati. Each character has a special power that will help the Cadets defeat Gordo.<ref name="home">[http://www.xmgstudio.com/?page_id=1738 Cannon Cadets main page] XMG Studios</ref>
== Game Features == * 80 levels * Level Builder *Cannon Cadets Academy (an online community that allows users to share or download levels) * 4 playable characters (RocketBoy, RocketGirl, Pop and Granati) * Hidden bonus levels <ref name="home" />
== Characters == * RocketBoy * RocketGirl * Pop * Granati * Gordo * Robot Army
== Device Requirements == Cannon Cadets is currently available for the iPhone, iPad and the iPod Touch with an iPad version to follow.<ref name="Cannon Cadets Press Release">[http://www.xmgstudio.com/?p=1847 "XMG Studio Blows the Lid Off the App Store with Cannon Cadets"] ''XMG Studio'', Retrieved August 18, 2010.</ref>
Requires Apple iOS version 3.1 or later.<ref name="Cannon Cadets iTunes Page">[https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/cannon-cadets/id383693833?mt=8 "Cannon Cadets iTunes page"] ''Apple'', Retrieved August 17, 2010.</ref>
