{{more citations needed|date=May 2017}}
A '''casino host''' is employed by a [[casino]] to deliver services to [[gamblers]] to help ensure that they become loyal [[Patrons#Commercial|patrons]].

==Nature of the work==

A casino host will usually try their best to please patrons of their casino and will do their best to fulfill any reasonable requests their clients might have. The casino host has the power to issue complimentary services (or "[[Comps (casino)|comps]]") to players. Comps can range from complimentary meals, beverages, and show ([[concert]] or [[theater]]) tickets right up to full accommodation in a [[hotel casino]]. A casino host will develop a relationship with every level of [[gambler]], from first-timers playing [[slot machine|quarter slots]] to high-profile multimillion-dollar gamblers (a [[high roller]]).

Comps issued by hosts vary greatly and can be anything from a free buffet coupon to luxurious villas and private charter flights to the casino.  The level and issuance of these comps by the host is done using mathematical formulas that calculate the theoretical loss of a player based on wager size, session length and the house edge of the game.  Based on this formula, the host will be authorized to re-invest a percentage of this theoretical win back into the player by issuing freebies with the aim to build a loyal relationship with the player.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vegasguy.com/casinos/casino-hosts/|title=Casino Hosts Las Vegas - Explanation & Overview of Host Duties|website=www.vegasguy.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-03-13}}</ref>

==Position in a casino==

The casino host reports directly to the [[marketing]] managers in most casinos. The casino host is the member of [[management]] that has the most contact with players and patrons.  The job of a casino host can be very competitive as they are seeking the repeat patronage of players, a common goal that is shared with competing casinos and their own casino hosts.

==In fiction==
The TV series ''[[Las Vegas (TV series)|Las Vegas]]'' has a [[Las Vegas (TV series)#Main cast and characters|main character]], Samantha Jane "Sam" Marquez, who is a casino host.

