'''Circurious''' is a cast of jugglers, singers, contortionists, singers, and dancers, which perform in various places in the United States, started in August 2008. They have been featured on several television shows such as [[Good Morning America]], [[David Letterman]], [[MTV]], [[ESPN]], and the New Year's Eve Party in [[Times Square]]. The acts include aerialists and acrobats, athletic performers, contortionists and other acts like singing and dancing. <ref>[http://www.symphonyspace.org/the-just-kidding-video-page symphonyspace.org, Circurious]</ref><ref>[http://herald-review.com/entertainment/local/circurious-strives-to-be-ultimate-variety-show/article_ef0386de-4258-11e3-8e8a-0019bb2963f4.html Herald Review, Circurious strives to be ultimate variety show, by Jim Vorel, Oct 31, 2013]</ref><ref>[http://smnewsnet.com/archives/54660/forty-eight-hours-of-non-stop-fun/ Southern Maryland News, Forty-Eight Hours of Non-Stop Fun, March 20, 2013]</ref><ref>[http://www.trademarkia.com/circurious-77695520.html trademarkia.com, Circurious]</ref><ref>[http://www2.cortland.edu/news/detail.dot?id=209961 American Circus and Variety Show Set, Home News News Detail, 03/31/2010]</ref>
