{{refimprove|date=August 2013}}

'''ColoringBook''' is a three-part series of recordings by composer [[Clayton Counts]].  Incorporating elements of [[Drone music|drone]], [[minimalism]], and [[found sound]], the records feature an array of instrumentalists, with a heavy focus on stringed and keyed instruments.

The project is regarded as a work of [[noise music]], though some of it is structurally similar to [[jazz]], [[contemporary classical music|contemporary classical]], or [[electroacoustic music]].  It is known for its use of [[Sound synthesis|synthesis]], layering, and [[spatial music|spatialization]].

