'''Exclusive ride time''' is a period aside by an [[amusement park]]  for exclusive access to one or more [[amusement ride]]s. Sessions may be scheduled outside of park operating hours or attractions may be closed off to the public during operating hours. Exclusive ride time has been allowed for private corporate events or celebrity functions<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/08/06/AR2006080600898.html|title=End of a Park Fit for the King|last=Emery|first=Theo|date=2006-08-07|access-date=2018-02-07|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref>, park sponsored groups such as annual passholders and roller coaster enthusiasts<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sanduskyregister.com/story/201712040007|title=Sandusky Register|website=www.sanduskyregister.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sixflags.com/greatamerica/special-events/exclusive-ride-time|title=Pass Holder Exclusive Ride Time (April 24 ) at Six Flags Great America|website=Six Flags Great America|language=en|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref>, special ticketed events, members of the media, or enthusiast groups such [[American Coaster Enthusiasts]].

DIsney theme parks brand exclusive ride time for guests staying in [[Walt Disney Parks and Resorts|on-site resorts]] as Extra Magic Hours.<ref>[http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/1946285 Tips to ensure magic, not meltdowns] [[MSNBC]]</ref>

